WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:01.920
I know I'm late tonight. I had some

00:00:01.920 --> 00:00:03.600
things come up, but we're going to go

00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:05.440
ahead and pray. I won't keep you very

00:00:05.440 --> 00:00:08.559
long, but there are some amazing things

00:00:08.559 --> 00:00:11.519
that happened in the news today. Braden

00:00:11.519 --> 00:00:13.200
was telling me about all the things that

00:00:13.200 --> 00:00:15.920
went on and the emails that were

00:00:15.920 --> 00:00:17.359
given to us. They said, 'Did you know

00:00:17.359 --> 00:00:19.840
this? Did you know that?' Folks, I'm

00:00:19.840 --> 00:00:21.520
telling you, the signs of the times are

00:00:21.520 --> 00:00:23.359
all around us. I mean, you just have to

00:00:23.359 --> 00:00:26.400
have your head in the sand or

00:00:26.400 --> 00:00:28.240
whatever if you're not looking at the

00:00:28.240 --> 00:00:29.840
signs of the times or where we are right

00:00:29.840 --> 00:00:33.280
now. Jesus Christ is coming, and you can

00:00:33.280 --> 00:00:36.960
see it if you have eyes to see, a

00:00:36.960 --> 00:00:38.879
heart to receive, and ears to hear,

00:00:38.879 --> 00:00:43.760
right? If you are looking and waiting,

00:00:43.760 --> 00:00:46.160
anticipating.

00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:48.640
So exciting. Exciting. I was going to

00:00:48.640 --> 00:00:52.320
show you this, Braden. I forgot.

00:00:52.320 --> 00:00:55.440
Maldonado sent this

00:00:55.440 --> 00:00:57.360
saying, 'Did you see this?' He wanted

00:00:57.360 --> 00:01:05.040
you to show the people. Let me show you.

00:01:05.040 --> 00:01:07.600
He wanted to show his—he told me because

00:01:07.600 --> 00:01:09.360
I was telling him congratulations on the

00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:12.159
million souls and said, 'Congratulations

00:01:12.159 --> 00:01:13.760
on the million people getting born

00:01:13.760 --> 00:01:16.720
again.' But he said that's 14 million

00:01:16.720 --> 00:01:19.680
souls since he's been starting out.

00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:20.799
Wow,

00:01:20.799 --> 00:01:23.280
14 million salvations.

00:01:23.280 --> 00:01:25.840
Just in my mind to wrap around that is

00:01:25.840 --> 00:01:27.439
incredible. I don't know how

00:01:27.439 --> 00:01:30.640
many Reinhard Bonnke got. But Reinhard

00:01:30.640 --> 00:01:33.520
Bonnke did a lot, but 14 million for

00:01:33.520 --> 00:01:38.159
anybody is a big number. But

00:01:38.159 --> 00:01:41.040
I'm on a race. I want to say it.

00:01:41.040 --> 00:01:42.720
What a challenge, huh?

00:01:42.720 --> 00:01:44.960
Our ministry in the name

00:01:44.960 --> 00:01:47.759
of Jesus will bring in over 50 million

00:01:47.759 --> 00:01:49.840
in the next year or so. Let's just say

00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:51.520
something big. I don't know. You don't

00:01:51.520 --> 00:01:53.840
want to limit God and say 50 million all

00:01:53.840 --> 00:01:55.759
together, but I want to say, hey,

00:01:55.759 --> 00:01:58.159
let's believe God for big. Somebody said

00:01:58.159 --> 00:01:59.920
we got a hundred million souls. I think

00:01:59.920 --> 00:02:01.360
it was a church in Minnesota that said

00:02:01.360 --> 00:02:04.240
they had a hundred million souls. And I

00:02:04.240 --> 00:02:07.119
was thinking, what? That's incredible.

00:02:07.119 --> 00:02:08.879
Is that right?

00:02:08.879 --> 00:02:10.800
Maybe I'm quoting that wrong, but

00:02:10.800 --> 00:02:13.040
it was a huge number. And then

00:02:13.040 --> 00:02:20.720
there's Tampa.

00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:26.400
Goodness gracious, Tampa, Braden.
